        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the publication of this letter in <hi rend="italic">Nature</hi>, 11 May 1876.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">A letter on the destruction of flowers by birds, written by <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_7622.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Alfred Reginald Pryor</ref>, was published in <hi rend="italic">Nature</hi>, 4 May 1876, p. 10. CD had described the same phenomenon with respect to primrose flowers in <hi rend="italic">Nature</hi>, 23 April 1874, p. 482, and 14 May 1874, pp. 24–5 (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 22, letters to <hi rend="italic">Nature</hi>, 18 April [1874] and 7 and 11 May [1874]).</note>
